data.title: Look into classes derived from RefCounted (and not Object) in JS packages other than "Atomic"
data.body:
There is an assert here as RefCounted classes will not have a uniqueID:

https://github.com/AtomicGameEngine/AtomicGameEngine/blob/master/Source/AtomicJS/Javascript/JSAPI.cpp#L75

Maybe we should add a static field to RefCounted so they do, currently this is only seems to be used when pushing a variant, which will push null on RefCounted anyway

data.title: AnimationController "Animation Resources" attr not valid for animated reimported models in scenes
data.body: The Animation Resources attribute probably needs to be split out to a referenced resource file as if an animated model is in a scene, and then reimported, currently no way to update with new animation data

data.title: Investigate Raspberry Pi support
data.body: I am looking for a game engine which can develop game, and can deploy it on different platform. I want to use Unity3D, but it seems not support raspberry pi. I know urho3D can run in raspberry pi, I don't know whether there was a plan to make AtomicGame engine support raspberry pi

data.title: Editor doesn't correctly handle resizing on windows
data.body:
When resizing the window, it often ends up with two black rects filling the space between the new and old size and the console is no longer accessible. This is easily reproducible using windows snapping to maximize it.
Snapping to the sides of the screen also fails to resize correctly.
